  "description": "MUST activate before writing/editing/deleting any class/id/function. 44 commands. v6.0.0: Android/Kotlin Revolution — Dedicated Kotlin parser (data class, sealed class, companion object, extension functions, suspend functions, properties, typealias, Android annotations), Android framework detection (Gradle, AndroidManifest.xml, Jetpack Compose, Hilt, Room, ViewModel, Zygisk, Xposed, NDK), Android component entrypoints (Activity, Service, BroadcastReceiver, ContentProvider, Application class), Android IPC API mapping (AIDL methods, ContentProvider URIs, BroadcastReceiver actions, Service binding, Messenger/Handler), Android state management (SharedPreferences, DataStore, Room, ViewModel, SavedStateHandle, Compose State, LiveData), Android project identity (app name from manifest, version from Gradle, monorepo detection). Kotlin and Java removed from unsupported_langs. Tested on topjohnwu/Magisk (8-language Android root framework with Zygisk injection).",  "author": "codelens",
